course_metadata.title: Practical Machine Learning for Building Applications

content_chunks.content: The course is intended for people who want to obtain the basic knowledge for working with data and be able to solve relevant practical problems. During the lectures, the course covers the basic theoretical and algorithmic foundations of data processing, analysis and modelling. The course encompasses fundamental concepts such as regression, classification, profiling, time series analysis, and control systems. Students will learn data processing and visualization principles, along with their software implementation. The course further addresses relevant energy-related problems and introduces appropriate techniques with a focus on technological solutions. Upon course completion, students will possess a comprehensive understanding of the methods and techniques necessary to address important modern challenges.

Machine learning technology for building data analytics - this course delivers comprehensive data science methodologies for building optimization and energy management applications. Technology for building digitalization includes advanced data science lifecycle management and visualization techniques, while machine learning fundamentals cover Artificial Neural Networks and predictive modeling for building performance optimization. The course introduces time series analysis for energy consumption forecasting and fault detection and diagnosis systems for building maintenance automation. Participants gain expertise in data cleaning processes, feature engineering techniques, and behind the meter technologies for energy monitoring and control. The curriculum covers data clustering algorithms for building categorization, control systems basics for automated building management, and intelligent control systems for adaptive energy optimization. Students develop skills in building data analytics, energy optimization techniques, and practical machine learning implementation for real-world building applications. The course prepares professionals to leverage data-driven approaches for enhanced building performance, reduced energy consumption, and improved operational efficiency through advanced analytics and automated control systems.
